  "title": "Digital Product Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Oversee the full product lifecycle, including defining vision, strategy, planning, and execution from ideation to delivery.</li>\n  <li>Guide product positioning and go-to-market strategies by understanding customer needs, analyzing trends, and collaborating with cross-functional teams.</li>\n  <li>Assess product performance and functionality, recommending enhancements and improvements based on data insights and user feedback.</li>\n  <li>Identify and evaluate potential partners or technology opportunities to expand product capabilities, strengthen market competitiveness, and drive user engagement.</li>\n  <li>Conduct market and industry research to uncover emerging technologies and business opportunities, and lead the preparation of proposals or business cases for new initiatives.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor’s Degree in any of the following disciplines (or related fields): Computer Science<br>\nInformation Technology, Programming &amp; Systems Analysis, and Computer Studies / Information Systems</li>\n  <li>A strong academic foundation in product management, digital systems, or technology innovation will be an advantage.</li>\n  <li>At least three (3) years of relevant experience in managing or leading digital products or platforms.</li>\n  <li>Proven track record in digital product management, including strategy development, user research, and product lifecycle execution.</li>\n  <li>Experience collaborating with cross-functional teams (engineering, UX/UI, marketing, and business stakeholders) to deliver impactful digital solutions.</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with Agile or Scrum methodologies and digital transformation initiatives is preferred</li>\n</ul>",
